      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALWAYS BE BLAKEY (8) came from this barrier for a resuming win at this circuit and distance three back and has placed over shorter trips in both outings here since. Should enjoy a nice trail and could prove hard to stop if he gets the gaps. TARA VICTORY NZ (4) took advantage of the ace draw when scoring here last week, getting home by a head. That was her third success from her last five starts so while drawn wider the form is hard to knock. A win looks imminent for TEN DA TOUCH NZ (3) having added to a string of top-four finishes when coming from the back row for second at this circuit and distance last week. Up in grade but better drawn. VINCENZO (7) won at this circuit and distance three back and there was plenty of merit in last week's effort when he came from this barrier for a 1.2m second. Chance again.",
